# Hostel Management Application
This is a Hostel Management Application built using the MERN (MongoDB, Express.js, React, Node.js) stack. It allows users to manage hostel facilities, room allocations, and resident details.

## Features
- Authentication: User authentication and authorization using JWT tokens.
- Dashboard: Overview of hostel occupancy, pending requests, and other relevant statistics.
- Room Management: CRUD operations for rooms, including adding new rooms, updating details, and deleting rooms.
- Resident Management: Managing resident details, including check-ins, check-outs, and room allocations.
- Maintenance Requests: System for residents to submit maintenance requests and track their status.

## Technologies Used
- Frontend: React, Redux (optional for state management)
- Backend: Node.js, Express.js
- Database: MongoDB with Mongoose for ORM
- Other Tools: JWT for authentication, Axios for API requests, Bootstrap or Material UI for styling.

## Prerequisites
- Node.js installed on your machine
- MongoDB installed locally or a cloud MongoDB instance (e.g., MongoDB Atlas)
- npm or yarn package manager

